```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "gin",
    "walltime": "12:00:00",
    "memory_per_cpu": "16G",
    "tasks": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 1,
    "gpus_per_task": 1,
    "nodes": 1,
    "working_directory": "/vols/opig/users/raja",
    "email": "arun.raja@dtc.ox.ac.uk",
    "email_type": "ALL",
    "partition": "nagagpu04-high-debug",
    "clusters": "all",
    "node": "nagagpu04.cpu.stats.ox.ac.uk",
    "output_file": "/vols/opig/users/raja/slurm_outs/slurm_%j.out",
    "error_file": "/vols/opig/users/raja/slurm_outs/slurm_%j.err",
    "conda_environment": "gin_conda",
    "python_packages": [
      "pandas",
      "torch",
      "torchvision",
      "torchaudio",
      "matplotlib",
      "numpy",
      "rdkit",
      "scikit_learn",
      "scipy",
      "seaborn",
      "spektral",
      "statsmodels",
      "tensorflow",
      "torch_geometric",
      "e3fp",
      "networkx",
      "optuna"
    ],
    "python_script": "GDL-ActivityCliff-3D/gin_exp.py",
    "script_arguments": [
      "--dataset",
      "postera_sars_cov_2_mpro",
      "--model",
      "knn"
    ],
    "output_file": "GDL-ActivityCliff-3D/terminal_output/gin_knn2.txt"
  }

```

This script is running under **Slurm**, a job scheduler and resource manager. The script sets up a job with the following parameters:

* **Job Name:** gin
* **Walltime:** 12 hours
* **Memory per CPU:** 16 GB
* **Number of Tasks:** 1
* **CPUs per Task:** 1
* **GPUs per Task:** 1
* **Number of Nodes:** 1
* **Working Directory:** /vols/opig/users/raja
* **Email Address:** arun.raja@dtc.ox.ac.uk
* **Email Type:** ALL (begin, end)
* **Partition:** nagagpu04-high-debug
* **Clusters:** all
* **Node:** nagagpu04.cpu.stats.ox.ac.uk
* **Output File:** /vols/opig/users/raja/slurm_outs/slurm_%j.out
* **Error File:** /vols/opig/users/raja/slurm_outs/slurm_%j.err

The script then activates a conda environment named `gin_conda` and installs a number of Python packages, including `pandas`, `torch`, `torchvision`, `torchaudio`, `matplotlib`, `numpy`, `rdkit`, `scikit_learn`, `scipy`, `seaborn`, `spektral`, `statsmodels`, `tensorflow`, `torch_geometric`, `e3fp`, `networkx`, and `optuna`. Finally, it runs the Python script `GDL-ActivityCliff-3D/gin_exp.py` with arguments `--dataset postera_sars_cov_2_mpro` and `--model knn`. The output of this script is redirected to the file `GDL-ActivityCliff-3D/terminal_output/gin_knn2.txt`.
